The '''Donetsk-Krivoy Rog Soviet Republic''' ({{lang-ru|<U+0414><U+043E><U+043D><U+0435><U+0446><U+043A><U+043E>-<U+041A><U+0440><U+0438><U+0432><U+043E><U+0440><U+043E><U+0436><U+0441><U+043A><U+0430><U+044F> <U+0441><U+043E><U+0432><U+0435><U+0442><U+0441><U+043A><U+0430><U+044F> <U+0440><U+0435><U+0441><U+043F><U+0443><U+0431><U+043B><U+0438><U+043A><U+0430>}}) was a short-lived [[soviet republic]], as part of the [[Russian SFSR]]. The republic was formed on [[February 18]], [[1918]]. The Donetsk-Krivoy Rog Soviet Republic claimed the territories south of neighbouring [[Ukrainian People's Republic]], which included the [[Donets Basin|Donbass]], [[Kharkiv|Kharkov]], and [[Yekaterinoslav Governorate]]s.

